<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3605] Ajax header-contribution omits IE conditional comments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3605</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have a header contributor which writes an IE conditional comment to the header response for an IE-specific stylesheet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the page is initially loaded, components on the page render with the IE conditional comment, and are displayed correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a component is added by an ajax request, the header contributor renders the conditional comment to the ajax response, but the conditional comment is omitted from the page output.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12503798">WICKET-3605</key>
            <summary>Ajax header-contribution omits IE conditional comments</summary>
